Sudanese Government Says 2,000 Civilians Were Killed By Rapid Support Forces In El-Fasher (18+ Videos)
Thousands of Sudanese civilians have been reportedly killed by the Rapid Support Forces (RSF) in el-Fashe after the withdrawal of the Sudanese Armed Forces (SAF) from the city in western Sudan.
Horrific videos purported to show RSF militants rounding up and executing civilians near el-Fasher began to surface online right after the fall of the city on October 26.
During a press conference in the city of Port Sudan on October 29, Mona Nour Al-Daem, Sudan's Deputy Commissioner of Humanitarian Aid, said that at least 2,000 civilians were killed by the RSF in el-Fasher, describing what happened as "genocide against unarmed civilians."

Over 130 Killed In Deadliest Police Raid In History Of Brazil (Videos)
Over 130 people, including several police officers, died in a massive raid by Brazilian security forces aimed at organized crime in Rio de Janeiro on October 28.
Rio de Janeiro State Governor Cláudio Castro told reporters at a press conference that police confiscated a “large quantity of drugs” in the raid, according to Reuters. Authorities also claimed on social media that 81 people were arrested and at least 42 rifles were seized during the operation.
Castro went on to pronounce the raid “the biggest operation in the history of Rio de Janeiro” in a post to the X social network.

Situation Is ‘Very Negative’ For Ukraine: Russian Forces Break Through Pokrovsk Line
Units of the «Center» group have taken control of the villages of Rog and Gnatovka, and are fighting for control of the industrial zone to the north of Pokrovsk. In Zaporizhzhia, the «East» grouping has seized control of the Vishnevoe area. 
The Ukrainian command is planning to withdraw its units from the Pokrovsk-Mirnograd district.
